@node Overview
@chapter Overview

@samp{claude-code-extras.el} extends @samp{claude-code}, the Emacs package that runs Claude Code sessions inside an Eat terminal buffer.  While @samp{claude-code} provides the core session management and terminal integration, this extras package layers on several quality-of-life features that make extended Claude sessions more manageable.

Several features (session switching, buffer protection, alerts, snippet insertion, terminal fixes) are shared with @samp{codex-extras.el} via the common @samp{ai-extras.el} package (@ref{Top,ai-extras,,ai-extras,}).  At load time, @samp{claude-code-extras.el} registers the Claude Code backend with @samp{ai-extras.el}, enabling a unified session switcher that shows sessions from all AI backends.  The backend icon is the official Claude sparkle logo rendered as an inline SVG via @code{ai-extras-svg-icon} (@ref{h:svg-icons,SVG icons,,ai-extras,}).

The package provides thirteen main areas of functionality:

@itemize
@item
@strong{Session switching.} A transient menu with persistent home-row key bindings for starting new Claude sessions or switching between existing ones (@ref{Session switching}).
@item
@strong{Status polling.} Integration with a statusline script that exports session metadata (model name, cost, context usage, token counts) as JSON, polled periodically and exposed through accessor functions (@ref{Status polling}).
@item
@strong{Usage polling.} Periodic polling of the Anthropic @samp{api/oauth/usage} endpoint to track 5-hour session and 7-day weekly utilization percentages, with accessor functions for modeline display and programmatic use (@ref{Usage polling}).
@item
@strong{Alerts.} Configurable OS notifications (visual, audible, or both) when Claude needs attention, triggered by the CLI's Notification hook event for idle prompts, permission requests, and elicitation dialogs.  The Notification hook is auto-configured in @samp{~/.claude/settings.json} at load time (@ref{Alerts}).
@item
@strong{Buffer lifecycle.} Kill protection for active sessions, automatic buffer cleanup on process exit, a SIGWINCH workaround for terminal rendering glitches, and a fix for @code{C-g} escape handling with multiple sessions (@ref{Buffer lifecycle}).
@item
@strong{Snippet insertion.} An adapter for @code{consult-yasnippet} that bypasses its direct buffer manipulation (which fails in Eat terminal buffers) and instead sends expanded snippet text through the terminal emulator (@ref{Snippet insertion}).
@item
@strong{Copilot integration.} An adapter that enables Copilot ghost-text prose completions while typing prompts in Claude Code buffers, routing accepted text through the terminal emulator (@ref{Copilot integration}).
@item
@strong{Skill runner.} Run any user-invocable Claude Code skill non-interactively from Emacs with completion, argument prompting, and a result buffer (@ref{Skill runner}).
@item
@strong{Batch TODO processing.} Sequential execution of org TODO entries via @samp{claude -p} in non-interactive mode, with logged results and a summary buffer (@ref{Batch TODO processing}).
@item
@strong{Interactive TODO sending.} Send the org TODO at point to a running interactive Claude Code session, with automatic project-based session resolution (@ref{Send TODO at point}).
@item
@strong{Branch navigation.} Create new branches from the current session and navigate the tree of sessions created by branching, with a tree-formatted display showing the branching structure and the ability to switch to or resume any branch (@ref{Branch navigation}).
@item
@strong{Project audit.} One-command comprehensive audit that sequentially runs code, design, and interpretability audit skills with auto-fix on the current project (@ref{Project audit}).
@item
@strong{Transient menu.} A transient dispatch menu that provides quick access to all commands, setup functions, and toggleable user options (@ref{Transient menu}).
@end itemize

The package depends on @samp{claude-code}, @samp{consult} (for branch navigation and snippet insertion), and @samp{paths} (for the batch log directory default).

